Gold\n\nThis rare resource is often used to train advanced military units and to fund research. Gold can be acquired by trading on the market or can be looted from other cities. It takes more time to loot gold than other resources during battle.
Wood\n\nA basic resource used for many purposes. Wood can be harvested from forests scattered throughout the world.
Crop\n\nA staple resource required for just about everything, including keeping your units alive. Crop can be acquired by laborers through Farms.
Iron\n\nAn ore used for advanced tasks. Iron can be acquired through the Refinery.
Troop Upkeep\n\nAmount of crop consumed every hour by your military units.

Defense Points\n\nDefense points are acquired when your units kill enemy units. These points are not only acquired when your city is attacked but also when your units fight while stationed in other player's cities.
Attack Points\n\nAttack points are acquired when you attack and kill enemy units.
Influence Points\n\nYour total influence points is the sum of all building levels in all of your cities.

Build a new city here. Requires Ox Wagons and Influence Points. Your total influence points is the sum of all building levels in all of your cities.  All Ox Wagons will be consumed to build the new city.
Units\n\nStatus of your military units. You can get more information about your units in the 'Unit Movement' screen.
